# Reusable Patterns

Use these patterns only when they match nearby code. Prefer the local implementation style over a generic template.

## Services

- Put interfaces in `interfaces/` and implementations in `implementations/`.
- Name service interfaces like `IAppInfoService` in `i_app_info_service.dart`.
- Register injectable implementations consistently with nearby services.
- Return existing result/error types used by the surrounding service.

## Pages And Widgets

- Public page class owns `Scaffold` and `AppBar`.
- Private child widget owns the body.
- Extract feature-specific widgets into the local `widgets` folder when the parent grows.
- Use `part`/`part of` only where the feature already uses that pattern.

## Tests

- Mirror the source path under `test`.
- Use existing `mocks.dart` before adding mock specs.
- Keep tests focused on behavior, especially regression cases.

## Repositories And Models

- Follow existing repository `interfaces/` and `implementation/` folders.
- Keep DTOs, database models, API models, enums, and mappers in `packages/models`.
- Use Freezed and generated JSON only where the surrounding models already do.
- Run generation through Melos; do not hand-edit generated files.

## Templates

- Use `.cursor/templates` as references, not as mandatory structure.
- Adapt templates to the current package and nearby code before editing.
